qas.question: Which newspaper did the The Sun on Sunday take the place of?
In what year was The Sun's look changed?
What was the circulation of The Sun on Sunday in March 2014?
When did the Sunday Mail overtake The Sun in sales numbers?
When is the weekly Mail forecast to pass The Sun in terms of circulation?

context: On 26 February 2012, The Sun on Sunday was launched to replace the closed <a0_0>News of the World<a0_0/>, employing some of its former journalists. In late <a1_0>2013<a1_0/>, it was given a new look, with a new typeface. The average circulation for The Sun on Sunday in March 2014 was <a2_0>1,686,840<a2_0/>; but in <a3_0>May 2015<a3_0/> The Mail on Sunday sold more copies for the first time, an average of 28,650 over those of its rival: 1,497,855 to 1,469,195. Roy Greenslade issued some caveats over the May 2015 figures, but believes the weekday Daily Mail will overtake The Sun in circulation <a4_0>during 2016<a4_0/>.
